WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.001 --> 00:00:02.645
Previously on will Trent…

2
00:00:02.669 --> 00:00:04.671
You have no sightings
of Adelaide trevens?

3
00:00:05.839 --> 00:00:07.925
Goodbye. will Trent.

4
00:00:08.884 --> 00:00:11.529
If you know where Antonio
morales is. you need to tell me.

5
00:00:13.347 --> 00:00:14.848
We'll be in touch.

6
00:00:16.558 --> 00:00:18.286
You think I'm holding out on you?

7
00:00:18.310 --> 00:00:22.499
Caroline. is there any new
intel on Adelaide trevens

8
00:00:22.523 --> 00:00:24.417
that we have not forwarded
to special agent Trent?

9
00:00:24.441 --> 00:00:27.212
No. ma'am. You gave me clear
instructions to share everything.

10
00:00:27.236 --> 00:00:31.674
I look at you and the career
you've had and what it's cost.

11
00:00:31.698 --> 00:00:33.784
I don't know if I can do this job anymore.

12
00:00:34.368 --> 00:00:36.304
If you tell anyone about this call.

13
00:00:36.328 --> 00:00:39.248
I'll remove your uncle's organs
with a rusty spoon and a smile.

14
00:00:39.831 --> 00:00:42.810
So be a good boy. special agent Trent.

15
00:00:42.834 --> 00:00:43.919
I'll be waiting.

16
00:00:47.339 --> 00:00:53.637
If you had to choose. would you
rather live on a star or in space?

17
00:00:55.514 --> 00:00:57.849
What? Like. alone?

18
00:00:59.726 --> 00:01:00.870
No. you can have friends.

19
00:01:00.894 --> 00:01:03.665
I hate being hot. Space.

20
00:01:03.689 --> 00:01:05.440
Me too.

21
00:01:06.900 --> 00:01:08.211
Is your edible hitting?

22
00:01:08.235 --> 00:01:11.947
I can't tell.

23
00:01:16.451 --> 00:01:17.512
Hide the gummies.

24
00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:25.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

25
00:01:28.964 --> 00:01:32.443
Whoa!

26
00:01:34.261 --> 00:01:35.596
Who the hell is that?

27
00:01:38.640 --> 00:01:40.868
The gummy is definitely hitting.

28
00:01:47.024 --> 00:01:49.460
It's just that I'm trying to
anticipate her next move.

29
00:01:49.484 --> 00:01:51.671
and I'm having trouble
getting inside her head.

30
00:01:51.695 --> 00:01:54.424
Yes. but I can't analyze
somebody I've never met.

31
00:01:54.448 --> 00:01:55.633
I'm your therapist.

32
00:01:55.657 --> 00:01:56.950
Come on. Dr. Roach.

33
00:01:57.534 --> 00:01:59.929
Look. I trust your opinion. Please.

34
00:01:59.953 --> 00:02:01.538
Flattery? Really?

35
00:02:02.372 --> 00:02:03.373
All right.

36
00:02:04.416 --> 00:02:06.686
- You're overthinking it.
- What do you mean?

37
00:02:06.710 --> 00:02:08.271
Will. from what you've told me.

38
00:02:08.295 --> 00:02:11.590
Adelaide's pathology is
dominated by two factors:

39
00:02:12.215 --> 00:02:15.385
Genetic predisposition
to antisocial behavior

40
00:02:15.886 --> 00:02:17.804
and overwhelming childhood trauma.

41
00:02:18.680 --> 00:02:20.450
Okay. what about her family history?

42
00:02:20.474 --> 00:02:24.353
The rejection of her father. her
need to control people the way he did?

43
00:02:24.853 --> 00:02:28.124
So you want to use those
details to construct a train of logic

44
00:02:28.148 --> 00:02:29.500
that you can hop on board

45
00:02:29.524 --> 00:02:32.944
and... choo choo! Ride all the
way to finding your uncle Antonio.

46
00:02:33.528 --> 00:02:36.257
Great. We're back to analyzing me again.

47
00:02:36.281 --> 00:02:39.177
Well. that's because you have
a brain that can be analyzed.

48
00:02:39.201 --> 00:02:41.220
Your behavior contains logic.

49
00:02:41.244 --> 00:02:46.333
That's not all. You feel
desire. empathy. guilt.

50
00:02:47.334 --> 00:02:50.087
Will Trent. you are a
deep. deep well of humanity.

51
00:02:51.630 --> 00:02:54.257
- You're saying Adelaide is different?
- Very different.

52
00:02:55.801 --> 00:03:01.366
A psychology as damaged as
hers. it's unpredictable. chaotic.

53
00:03:01.390 --> 00:03:03.159
You're an amazing detective.

54
00:03:03.183 --> 00:03:06.496
but even you will not be
able to piece together exactly

55
00:03:06.520 --> 00:03:09.624
what she wants from you. because
I don't think she knows either.

56
00:03:09.648 --> 00:03:11.918
I mean. think about
when you first met her.

57
00:03:11.942 --> 00:03:16.089
She was pretending to be law
enforcement. You're a special agent.

58
00:03:16.113 --> 00:03:19.199
She was trying on the
experience of being you.

59
00:03:19.991 --> 00:03:22.970
Then came the flirting. I don't
know if you want to dig into that.

60
00:03:22.994 --> 00:03:24.722
No. I do not.

61
00:03:24.746 --> 00:03:28.125
Then she forced you to relive the
circumstances of your mother's death.

62
00:03:28.834 --> 00:03:30.634
I'm very sorry that she
did that. by the way.

63
00:03:31.878 --> 00:03:34.273
Yeah. Me too.

64
00:03:34.297 --> 00:03:36.425
Then she tried to kill
you. A few times. you said.

65
00:03:37.050 --> 00:03:38.861
No. just twice.

66
00:03:38.885 --> 00:03:41.513
So you're saying she's crazy. right?

67
00:03:42.097 --> 00:03:44.158
Will. you know. I don't
really like to use that word.

68
00:03:44.182 --> 00:03:48.871
So at any point. she might be trying
to be me. screw me. trick me or kill me.

69
00:03:48.895 --> 00:03:50.105
I mean. that's pretty crazy.

70
00:03:50.730 --> 00:03:53.150
And you won't know which.

71
00:04:00.282 --> 00:04:04.095
What about this? "Real estate
operations and financing"?

72
00:04:04.119 --> 00:04:07.181
No. no. no. no. no. You're not
going to be a real estate agent.

73
00:04:07.205 --> 00:04:09.183
Why not? I watch enough hgtv.

74
00:04:09.207 --> 00:04:11.394
Because real estate
agents need to be chipper.

75
00:04:11.418 --> 00:04:13.438
and you dole out smiles
like they cost you money.

76
00:04:13.462 --> 00:04:16.899
Yeah. well. maybe I would smile more if
I wasn't confronted with death every day.

77
00:04:16.923 --> 00:04:20.194
I joined the apd because
my mom was a cop.

78
00:04:20.218 --> 00:04:22.947
and then I was pushed into
gbi because of my aunt Mandy.

79
00:04:22.971 --> 00:04:26.492
I just feel like sometimes
my life happened

80
00:04:26.516 --> 00:04:29.060
without me making any
decisions along the way.

81
00:04:29.561 --> 00:04:31.330
I want to take control of my future.

82
00:04:31.354 --> 00:04:34.375
You know how many people depend
on the gbi? Your job's important.

83
00:04:34.399 --> 00:04:36.878
Yeah. a lot of jobs are
important. People need houses.

84
00:04:36.902 --> 00:04:40.298
Interesting. fun. and
every day is different.

85
00:04:40.322 --> 00:04:43.342
I could get killed on the job at any time.

86
00:04:43.366 --> 00:04:46.596
I want to grow old enough to
see my kid win a grammy one day.

87
00:04:46.620 --> 00:04:48.139
You know what? Fine.

88
00:04:48.163 --> 00:04:51.309
Leave the gbi. follow your
bliss. and go to bed every night

89
00:04:51.333 --> 00:04:53.352
and try not to think about all
the people who won't get justice

90
00:04:53.376 --> 00:04:56.336
- because you're not on the job.
- What do you care. as long as I pay rent?

91
00:04:59.716 --> 00:05:01.343
I gotta get this. Sorry.

92
00:05:02.093 --> 00:05:03.345
What's up. Austin?

93
00:05:05.347 --> 00:05:08.517
Is everyone okay? Yeah.
yeah. I'll be right there.

94
00:05:09.226 --> 00:05:11.978
Old army buddy. His
teenager just got carjacked.

95
00:05:12.854 --> 00:05:15.398
I told him I would help him. but…

96
00:05:15.941 --> 00:05:18.151
Max has your car for the night.

97
00:05:19.110 --> 00:05:21.238
- Right.
- And you need to borrow mine.

98
00:05:22.280 --> 00:05:27.178
For justice and honor…
…and the order of society.

99
00:05:27.202 --> 00:05:30.288
And I'll get you a burrito from
Jimmy's bean shack on the way back.

100
00:05:32.457 --> 00:05:33.542
Okay.

101
00:05:42.259 --> 00:05:44.862
- You said you got carjacked.
- We did.

102
00:05:44.886 --> 00:05:46.739
Austin. truck's right there.

103
00:05:46.763 --> 00:05:48.115
Yeah. but she locked herself inside.

104
00:05:48.139 --> 00:05:50.201
and these two dumbasses
left the keys in the ignition.

105
00:05:50.225 --> 00:05:51.393
That's car-squatting.

106
00:05:51.977 --> 00:05:53.955
- What happened?
- She didn't say anything.

107
00:05:53.979 --> 00:05:56.249
She just jumped in the
truck and locked the doors.

108
00:05:56.273 --> 00:06:00.211
- And you don't know her?
- I think she's a junkie. She is not right.

109
00:06:00.235 --> 00:06:02.338
She hasn't said a word this entire time.

110
00:06:02.362 --> 00:06:05.216
Hold on. She doesn't
look high to me. Let me try.

111
00:06:16.543 --> 00:06:17.752
Hi.

112
00:06:18.712 --> 00:06:22.257
Are you hungry? I have granola bars.

113
00:06:24.926 --> 00:06:26.344
Do you like Berry or peanut butter?

114
00:06:34.311 --> 00:06:38.231
My name is faith. I'm here to help you.

115
00:06:39.983 --> 00:06:41.234
Can you tell me what you need?

116
00:06:43.612 --> 00:06:46.364
Okay. Can you tell me your name?

117
00:06:51.494 --> 00:06:53.139
You're not in any trouble.

118
00:06:53.163 --> 00:06:55.248
I just want to make sure that you're okay.

119
00:06:56.333 --> 00:06:57.667
Are you still hungry?

120
00:06:59.711 --> 00:07:02.714
How about you open the door.
and I can give you the other bar?

121
00:07:20.523 --> 00:07:22.859
You don't have any shoes
on. How'd you get here?

122
00:07:28.073 --> 00:07:29.366
Aliens.

123
00:07:30.075 --> 00:07:32.619
- What was that?
- The aliens took me.

124
00:07:56.184 --> 00:07:57.268
Well?

125
00:07:59.354 --> 00:08:02.291
A woman matching Adelaide
trevens's physical profile

126
00:08:02.315 --> 00:08:06.003
was spotted crossing the
anzalduas port of entry into Texas.

127
00:08:06.027 --> 00:08:07.427
Does the FBI know where she is now?

128
00:08:07.946 --> 00:08:09.674
- We're working on it.
- Was she alone?

129
00:08:09.698 --> 00:08:12.134
Is there any reason to believe
that Antonio morales is with her?

130
00:08:12.158 --> 00:08:13.785
We don't know that yet.

131
00:08:14.994 --> 00:08:16.389
Has your agent Trent heard from her?

132
00:08:16.413 --> 00:08:18.832
No. I would have told you if he had.

133
00:08:20.250 --> 00:08:21.918
Are you sure he would tell you?

134
00:08:23.628 --> 00:08:25.856
I'd be a lot more
confident in your answer

135
00:08:25.880 --> 00:08:28.192
if he would simply let
us monitor that phone.

136
00:08:28.216 --> 00:08:30.152
He doesn't trust the FBI.

137
00:08:30.176 --> 00:08:32.238
He knows you're more interested
in apprehending Adelaide

138
00:08:32.262 --> 00:08:33.322
than finding his uncle.

139
00:08:33.346 --> 00:08:34.657
She killed one of ours.

140
00:08:34.681 --> 00:08:37.326
Is that the reason for these spy games?

141
00:08:37.350 --> 00:08:40.621
You know. I had to pull in a
decade-old iou to get you to talk to me.

142
00:08:40.645 --> 00:08:42.498
and even then it's like this.

143
00:08:42.522 --> 00:08:45.275
I feel like I'm buying drugs.

144
00:08:46.192 --> 00:08:47.902
Do you guys have any actionable leads?

145
00:08:49.029 --> 00:08:50.447
We made progress on one thing.

146
00:08:51.948 --> 00:08:53.884
We compiled a list of persons of interest

147
00:08:53.908 --> 00:08:55.868
for the young man who
gave agent Trent the phone.

148
00:08:56.911 --> 00:08:58.597
- The commander?
- Yeah.

149
00:08:58.621 --> 00:09:00.999
It's a long list. but we're
working on whittling it down.

150
00:09:01.750 --> 00:09:02.751
In the meantime…

151
00:09:04.627 --> 00:09:05.628
I know.

152
00:09:07.338 --> 00:09:08.899
This stays between us.

153
00:09:19.517 --> 00:09:20.953
- Hey.
- Hey.

154
00:09:20.977 --> 00:09:23.748
Still no ID. If she's from the
area. no one's looking for her.

155
00:09:23.772 --> 00:09:26.250
I asked Angie to expand
the search nationwide.

156
00:09:26.274 --> 00:09:27.776
Was she sexually assaulted?

157
00:09:28.359 --> 00:09:30.779
Don't know. She won't
let doctors examine her.

158
00:09:32.530 --> 00:09:34.800
- Hi. How is she?
- Hi.

159
00:09:34.824 --> 00:09:38.429
She says she can't remember her
name or anything that happened to her.

160
00:09:38.453 --> 00:09:40.473
She says that the
aliens wiped her memory.

161
00:09:40.497 --> 00:09:42.224
You think she's lying
to protect someone?

162
00:09:42.248 --> 00:09:44.518
She looks shook up
to me. Maybe PTSD?

163
00:09:44.542 --> 00:09:45.853
It could be.

164
00:09:45.877 --> 00:09:48.898
What is she doing? Drawing?

165
00:09:48.922 --> 00:09:50.816
I left her a notepad.

166
00:09:50.840 --> 00:09:54.511
You know. sometimes when a patient
won't talk. they'll write or draw instead.

167
00:09:55.011 --> 00:09:56.572
It's actually a really good sign.

168
00:09:56.596 --> 00:09:58.973
- If you'll excuse me. I'll be back.
- Thank you.

169
00:10:00.975 --> 00:10:02.787
You know you don't have
to assist on this. right?

170
00:10:02.811 --> 00:10:03.913
Yeah. it's okay.

171
00:10:03.937 --> 00:10:07.041
Will's out with a bug that's been
going around. and I'm between cases.

172
00:10:07.065 --> 00:10:09.192
No. I mean. seeing as you
have one foot out the door.

173
00:10:11.236 --> 00:10:14.364
Remember that time you told
me you hadn't pooped in six days?

174
00:10:16.366 --> 00:10:17.426
How is that relevant?

175
00:10:17.450 --> 00:10:20.179
Did I bring it up every five minutes
while you were trying to work?

176
00:10:20.203 --> 00:10:22.389
No. You told me to eat more fiber.

177
00:10:22.413 --> 00:10:25.583
That's right. There's a
lesson in there. You'll find it.

178
00:10:26.084 --> 00:10:28.062
I told you that in confidence.

179
00:10:34.467 --> 00:10:38.847
Hi. I brought you some pants.
Hospital gowns are the worst.

180
00:10:40.515 --> 00:10:44.394
Do you want to hear a story
about my dog when I was a kid?

181
00:10:47.021 --> 00:10:51.651
Okay. so my mom brought
him home from work one day.

182
00:10:52.610 --> 00:10:56.090
He had three legs and one
eye. His name was gremlin.

183
00:10:56.114 --> 00:10:58.676
He had a lot of mortal enemies.

184
00:10:58.700 --> 00:11:03.371
including the vacuum cleaner. the
mailman. any set of stairs and rain.

185
00:11:04.247 --> 00:11:05.623
but he loved me.

186
00:11:06.666 --> 00:11:09.627
He would sleep right here.

187
00:11:10.837 --> 00:11:11.838
Every night.

188
00:11:12.630 --> 00:11:16.467
He kept me warm and safe.

189
00:11:18.386 --> 00:11:20.346
You want to see what he looked like?

190
00:11:29.105 --> 00:11:30.481
Do you like to draw?

191
00:11:34.611 --> 00:11:36.070
Can I see?

192
00:11:47.123 --> 00:11:48.124
Thank you.

193
00:11:52.128 --> 00:11:53.838
That's the one that watched me.

194
00:11:58.927 --> 00:11:59.928
It's a sign.

195
00:12:00.470 --> 00:12:02.990
A sign? That we should
call mulder and Scully?

196
00:12:03.014 --> 00:12:05.034
No. dummy. it's a literal sign.

197
00:12:05.058 --> 00:12:08.078
Shelly's alien emporium off the
freeway in grove park. Come on.

198
00:12:22.367 --> 00:12:24.261
You're right. That's the alien.

199
00:12:24.285 --> 00:12:26.639
Maybe this is where she was taken from.

200
00:12:26.663 --> 00:12:27.765
This place looks incredible.

201
00:12:27.789 --> 00:12:29.683
Look at all the satellite
dishes on the roof.

202
00:12:29.707 --> 00:12:31.518
What does Shelly know that we don't?

203
00:12:31.542 --> 00:12:33.461
Hopefully something
about our Jane Doe.

204
00:12:40.468 --> 00:12:43.012
- This place is...
- a lot.

205
00:12:43.763 --> 00:12:45.139
I was gonna say "amazing."

206
00:12:53.106 --> 00:12:58.712
Welcome to Shelly's alien emporium.

207
00:12:58.736 --> 00:13:01.465
Georgia's oldest and
most comprehensive library

208
00:13:01.489 --> 00:13:04.301
of extraterrestrial documentation.

209
00:13:04.325 --> 00:13:05.511
I'm Shelly.

210
00:13:05.535 --> 00:13:08.621
Hi. Shelly. We. have a
few questions for you.

211
00:13:09.205 --> 00:13:10.581
Well. it's about time.

212
00:13:11.249 --> 00:13:17.940
February 8. 1972. I was taken
from a Montgomery ward parking lot.

213
00:13:17.964 --> 00:13:20.234
They kept me for nine
days. ran their tests.

214
00:13:20.258 --> 00:13:22.945
and put me back down
behind the Clermont lounge

215
00:13:22.969 --> 00:13:25.864
in completely different clothes.

216
00:13:25.888 --> 00:13:30.786
It's all here in my book. alienated.

217
00:13:30.810 --> 00:13:33.038
We're actually here to
talk about a missing girl.

218
00:13:33.062 --> 00:13:35.416
Yeah. she said she was abducted too.

219
00:13:35.440 --> 00:13:38.502
Greens or grays? Any missing
time? Where'd they take her from?

220
00:13:38.526 --> 00:13:42.131
Maybe around here. She
actually drew a picture of your sign.

221
00:13:42.155 --> 00:13:45.592
Here? No. No way. I-I
would have picked it up.

222
00:13:45.616 --> 00:13:47.886
- With your satellite dishes?
- That's right.

223
00:13:47.910 --> 00:13:52.599
I'll be the first to know when another
ship hits the greater southeast airspace.

224
00:13:52.623 --> 00:13:54.351
Do you have any video
cameras up there. Shelly?

225
00:13:54.375 --> 00:13:58.856
No. no. no. By the time they're close
enough for video. well. you'll know it.

226
00:13:58.880 --> 00:14:01.442
You'll taste them first. Licorice.

227
00:14:01.466 --> 00:14:04.403
That's how you know they're close.

228
00:14:04.427 --> 00:14:06.697
You won't hear the ship. It's silent.

229
00:14:06.721 --> 00:14:11.035
But you'll feel a humming
in your squishy bits.

230
00:14:11.059 --> 00:14:12.119
Okay.

231
00:14:12.143 --> 00:14:14.496
Our Jane Doe didn't mention that.

232
00:14:14.520 --> 00:14:16.147
Have you ever seen this girl before?

233
00:14:17.231 --> 00:14:19.460
Her? Yeah. I've seen her.

234
00:14:19.484 --> 00:14:23.362
Down the street. coming out of
that hotel diner with her grandma.

235
00:14:24.030 --> 00:14:25.340
Her grandma?

236
00:14:25.364 --> 00:14:27.634
Yeah. or seemed like her grandma.

237
00:14:27.658 --> 00:14:33.015
Sometimes aliens shape-shift.
so you never can be sure.

238
00:14:33.039 --> 00:14:35.768
Maybe a week ago.

239
00:14:35.792 --> 00:14:40.922
I remember. 'cause
she was staring at me all

240
00:14:41.839 --> 00:14:43.382
haunted-like.

241
00:14:51.265 --> 00:14:52.266
This is her room.

242
00:14:52.934 --> 00:14:54.519
The vines are the curtains.

243
00:14:56.312 --> 00:15:00.000
Okay. Hey. we're gonna need the
registration information for this room.

244
00:15:00.024 --> 00:15:01.192
Yeah. I'll get it for you.

245
00:15:01.901 --> 00:15:04.505
Okay. luggage is gone.
Room has been cleaned.

246
00:15:04.529 --> 00:15:06.489
Looks like they checked
out. but where's grandma?

247
00:15:08.908 --> 00:15:12.787
Hey. Polaski. can you send a crime scene
unit to the sleep away inn in grove park?

248
00:15:13.621 --> 00:15:14.622
Yeah. thanks.

249
00:15:17.208 --> 00:15:18.543
Hey. faith. Look at this.

250
00:15:24.549 --> 00:15:25.925
No shower curtain.

251
00:15:33.349 --> 00:15:34.475
We found grandma.

252
00:16:03.504 --> 00:16:04.565
Adelaide.

253
00:16:04.589 --> 00:16:06.924
I do love how you say my name.

254
00:16:08.050 --> 00:16:12.114
There's always a little
something in the way you say it.

255
00:16:12.138 --> 00:16:14.599
- Contempt?
- You can only hate the things you love.

256
00:16:17.935 --> 00:16:20.396
Guess what I'm holding right now.

257
00:16:22.565 --> 00:16:25.210
My god. Don't worry.

258
00:16:25.234 --> 00:16:27.695
What did you think?
It was Antonio's head?

259
00:16:28.946 --> 00:16:30.281
It's a matchbox.

260
00:16:34.035 --> 00:16:36.513
Yeah. The bar in Puerto Rico.

261
00:16:36.537 --> 00:16:37.747
I carry it with me.

262
00:16:39.874 --> 00:16:40.958
I like to touch it.

263
00:16:43.836 --> 00:16:46.631
I saw you watching
me dance that night. will.

264
00:16:47.924 --> 00:16:54.180
Wishing you could take me.
move me however you chose.

265
00:16:54.931 --> 00:16:57.183
- Tell me I'm wrong.
- No.

266
00:16:58.559 --> 00:16:59.727
You're not wrong.

267
00:17:02.772 --> 00:17:03.940
I wanna see you.

268
00:17:05.691 --> 00:17:06.776
Tomorrow?

269
00:17:07.526 --> 00:17:08.903
I'd like that very much.

270
00:17:10.863 --> 00:17:12.615
How do you feel about small plates?

271
00:17:13.282 --> 00:17:16.637
I don't usually like to
share. but I would with you.

272
00:17:16.661 --> 00:17:18.663
Well. I don't want to
share you with anyone.

273
00:17:20.706 --> 00:17:23.894
What about my uncle?
I need proof of life.

274
00:17:23.918 --> 00:17:25.461
We'll discuss over dinner.

275
00:17:26.796 --> 00:17:28.506
Le bon nosh. 8:00 P.M.

276
00:17:29.257 --> 00:17:33.302
Come alone. and for god's
sake. don't tell anyone.

277
00:17:34.720 --> 00:17:36.097
That'll just piss me off.

278
00:17:36.722 --> 00:17:39.475
Of course. It'll be good to see you.

279
00:17:40.059 --> 00:17:41.060
And…

280
00:17:43.062 --> 00:17:45.523
Adelaide… yes?

281
00:17:48.025 --> 00:17:52.321
Don't shower. I liked how
you smelled in the jungle.

282
00:17:55.074 --> 00:17:56.325
Goodbye. will.

283
00:18:00.454 --> 00:18:04.851
So our grandma is Denise
hensley. 55 years old.

284
00:18:04.875 --> 00:18:07.646
Record goes back decades.
mostly solicitation and pandering.

285
00:18:07.670 --> 00:18:09.940
I'm sorry. When did you take my office?

286
00:18:09.964 --> 00:18:12.484
I am on desk duty.
and you are in the field.

287
00:18:12.508 --> 00:18:14.861
So it only makes sense. I requisitioned it.

288
00:18:14.885 --> 00:18:18.115
Hey. guys. I got Pete's autopsy report.

289
00:18:18.139 --> 00:18:19.866
Cause of death was blunt-force trauma.

290
00:18:19.890 --> 00:18:21.827
One of the blows severed
her vertebral artery.

291
00:18:21.851 --> 00:18:22.953
It could have been intentional.

292
00:18:22.977 --> 00:18:25.080
So the two of them were together.

293
00:18:25.104 --> 00:18:28.417
bad guys came in. beat up Denise
hensley. and the girl escaped.

294
00:18:28.441 --> 00:18:32.337
Not quite. Time of death was
approximately 16 hours ago.

295
00:18:32.361 --> 00:18:34.339
She was killed after
our Jane Doe escaped?

296
00:18:34.363 --> 00:18:36.466
- Or maybe because she escaped?
- Yes.

297
00:18:36.490 --> 00:18:40.846
And she's not the girl's
grandma or mother or aunt.

298
00:18:40.870 --> 00:18:43.623
Not by blood. anyway. No shared DNA.

299
00:18:46.125 --> 00:18:48.186
Can I get a peanut M&M?

300
00:18:48.210 --> 00:18:51.130
Yeah. give us two minutes.
shortstop. I'll put it on your tab.

301
00:18:51.631 --> 00:18:53.049
Thanks. Polaski.

302
00:18:54.008 --> 00:18:56.695
What was that? They knock for you?

303
00:18:56.719 --> 00:18:59.680
Guys. there is one more piece to
this that I think you should know.

304
00:19:00.431 --> 00:19:02.975
Doctors came back with
Jane Doe's medical records.

305
00:19:03.684 --> 00:19:06.288
They found signs of sexual assault.

306
00:19:10.775 --> 00:19:12.735
Denise hensley was her manager.

307
00:19:13.402 --> 00:19:15.655
Kept her captive. sent
money up the chain.

308
00:19:16.405 --> 00:19:17.758
She was being sex trafficked.

309
00:19:17.782 --> 00:19:19.051
Damn it.

310
00:19:19.075 --> 00:19:22.536
Girl managed to get away.
Bosses beat and killed Denise.

311
00:19:25.039 --> 00:19:26.540
I liked it better when it was aliens.

312
00:19:29.919 --> 00:19:32.147
"The room appeared
excessively cleaned.

313
00:19:32.171 --> 00:19:35.525
They found no visible
fingerprints. no biological material.

314
00:19:35.549 --> 00:19:37.819
no trace evidence. no random fibers."

315
00:19:37.843 --> 00:19:40.822
That's… …that's pretty
clean for a two-star hotel.

316
00:19:40.846 --> 00:19:42.824
I mean. what do you expect? Roaches?

317
00:19:42.848 --> 00:19:45.077
One negative yelp review.
corporate will come for my head.

318
00:19:45.101 --> 00:19:47.204
Yeah? What did corporate have
to say about the security cameras

319
00:19:47.228 --> 00:19:48.580
being conveniently nonfunctional?

320
00:19:48.604 --> 00:19:51.416
Yeah. that's been an issue. We've
had a ticket open on that forever.

321
00:19:51.440 --> 00:19:53.001
A ticket!

322
00:19:53.025 --> 00:19:56.338
Tucker. a girl was sex trafficked
in your hotel right under your nose.

323
00:19:56.362 --> 00:19:57.923
and you're telling me
you didn't even notice?

324
00:19:57.947 --> 00:20:00.950
Because it looks to me like you
are a party to human trafficking.

325
00:20:02.159 --> 00:20:03.345
- Wait.
- You're in this.

326
00:20:03.369 --> 00:20:05.430
It's time you start
telling us what you know.

327
00:20:05.454 --> 00:20:07.641
God. I didn't really think that they were...

328
00:20:07.665 --> 00:20:09.250
of course you did!

329
00:20:09.750 --> 00:20:11.544
Did you see the men coming and going?

330
00:20:12.128 --> 00:20:13.838
Did you see the bruises on her body?

331
00:20:14.839 --> 00:20:16.090
What kept you quiet?

332
00:20:18.259 --> 00:20:19.260
Did they pay you off?

333
00:20:19.844 --> 00:20:21.679
Or did you just not want
to make any waves?

334
00:20:22.471 --> 00:20:25.701
It was an envelope of money every week.

335
00:20:26.851 --> 00:20:29.246
- Who rented that room?
- I don't know his name.

336
00:20:29.270 --> 00:20:31.456
Was he the one who beat
Denise hensley to death?

337
00:20:31.480 --> 00:20:32.749
I don't know anything about that.

338
00:20:32.773 --> 00:20:36.378
It is against policy to rent a
room to somebody without an ID.

339
00:20:36.402 --> 00:20:39.047
Corporate wanted us to fill as
many rooms as possible. all right?

340
00:20:39.071 --> 00:20:41.967
They-they-they would give us
bonuses. They didn't care about the girls.

341
00:20:41.991 --> 00:20:44.118
Wait. what? Girls?

342
00:20:47.037 --> 00:20:48.122
There were others?

343
00:20:49.999 --> 00:20:53.562
We searched that place
high and low. Tucker.

344
00:20:53.586 --> 00:20:54.754
Where are they?

345
00:20:55.463 --> 00:20:57.232
I don't know. I don't know. okay?

346
00:20:57.256 --> 00:20:59.508
I really don't know. I'm
sorry. I-I-I don't know.

347
00:21:00.384 --> 00:21:02.404
Well. you can think about it
while you're being processed.

348
00:21:02.428 --> 00:21:04.489
because you are under arrest.

349
00:21:04.513 --> 00:21:05.890
Stand up.

350
00:21:13.230 --> 00:21:15.041
You can go home if
you want. It's getting late.

351
00:21:15.065 --> 00:21:16.668
I'm sure Seth wants to see you.

352
00:21:16.692 --> 00:21:18.962
He will see plenty of me
when this baby comes.

353
00:21:18.986 --> 00:21:20.696
I want to help.

354
00:21:23.157 --> 00:21:25.761
- This one's getting in my bones. Angie.
- I get it.

355
00:21:25.785 --> 00:21:27.596
Trafficking cases will
keep you up at night.

356
00:21:27.620 --> 00:21:32.833
These girls being sold like meat.
Used and discarded like trash.

357
00:21:34.502 --> 00:21:36.378
Some of them are just little kids.

358
00:21:37.254 --> 00:21:38.607
I don't know how they survive it.

359
00:21:38.631 --> 00:21:39.632
A lot of them don't.

360
00:21:42.051 --> 00:21:43.219
Some of us do.

361
00:21:52.645 --> 00:21:55.791
Wait. I… I think. Angie…

362
00:21:55.815 --> 00:21:59.336
I think this is… is this her? Is this her?

363
00:22:01.070 --> 00:22:02.130
This is her. right?

364
00:22:02.154 --> 00:22:04.508
- Yes. Yes.
- It is. It is. You found her.

365
00:22:04.532 --> 00:22:07.511
Grace elverton. Her parents
reported her missing last year.

366
00:22:07.535 --> 00:22:10.246
She went to an art festival
and never came home.

367
00:22:11.580 --> 00:22:13.290
Till now.

368
00:22:17.169 --> 00:22:19.898
All right. the background
is Caribbean blue.

369
00:22:22.216 --> 00:22:24.653
And along the backside. that's
where we have the bar's address.

370
00:22:24.677 --> 00:22:26.196
It's small. yellow. and along the bottom.

371
00:22:26.220 --> 00:22:28.615
It should match the website's font.

372
00:22:28.639 --> 00:22:30.826
You know what? Let's.
crush up the box a little bit.

373
00:22:30.850 --> 00:22:33.078
you know. blunt the edges.
make it look a little torn.

374
00:22:33.102 --> 00:22:36.873
and the tracker... this is important...
has to be impossible to notice.

375
00:22:36.897 --> 00:22:39.584
Okay? No added weight. no bulging...

376
00:22:39.608 --> 00:22:41.753
- yeah.
- Hey. you paying attention?

377
00:22:41.777 --> 00:22:44.238
Yeah. yeah. Yeah. Is your…

378
00:22:44.738 --> 00:22:46.031
Is your dog… …a biter?

379
00:22:49.243 --> 00:22:52.037
- Well. she only bites people who lie.
- No kidding.

380
00:22:52.872 --> 00:22:55.600
Can you deliver this
tomorrow by 4:00 P.M. or not?

381
00:22:55.624 --> 00:22:58.979
- Yeah. man. We're good.
- With a range of one mile.

382
00:22:59.003 --> 00:23:01.731
Yeah. man.

383
00:23:01.755 --> 00:23:03.942
Okay. all right. Look.
more like a thousand feet.

384
00:23:03.966 --> 00:23:07.153
Look. dude. you want invisible
and you want a rush job. all right?

385
00:23:07.177 --> 00:23:09.346
You want better? Go use your guys.

386
00:23:12.850 --> 00:23:13.851
Will?

387
00:23:14.393 --> 00:23:16.580
We gotta go to the back. We
gotta go to the back right now.

388
00:23:16.604 --> 00:23:18.272
Let's go. Come on.

389
00:23:19.231 --> 00:23:20.625
Wait. where's my money?

390
00:23:20.649 --> 00:23:23.587
Okay. look. here's half. All
right. you get the rest on delivery.

391
00:23:23.611 --> 00:23:24.671
What about the deal we made?

392
00:23:24.695 --> 00:23:27.489
Consider it an incentive to be
on time. Now go. Get out of here.

393
00:23:30.826 --> 00:23:32.053
Will.

394
00:23:32.077 --> 00:23:34.747
- Are you in there?
- Coming.

395
00:23:37.291 --> 00:23:40.336
- What are you doing here?
- Checking on you. You gonna let me in?

396
00:23:46.050 --> 00:23:48.761
I had this bad feeling
you weren't really sick.

397
00:23:50.095 --> 00:23:53.325
What? You want a doctor's note?

398
00:23:53.349 --> 00:23:58.079
You have anything? FBI
share any new intel with you?

399
00:24:00.940 --> 00:24:01.941
Not yet.

400
00:24:03.442 --> 00:24:05.861
I'm sorry Adelaide
hasn't called you yet. will.

401
00:24:08.113 --> 00:24:09.174
Yeah.

402
00:24:09.198 --> 00:24:11.051
Why don't you let the
FBI monitor the phone?

403
00:24:11.075 --> 00:24:12.427
Absolutely not.

404
00:24:12.451 --> 00:24:15.597
It's a good idea. You
shouldn't shoulder this alone.

405
00:24:15.621 --> 00:24:18.958
They'll go after her.
and they'll get him killed.

406
00:24:19.541 --> 00:24:20.793
You know this.

407
00:24:26.840 --> 00:24:29.426
I think about how he
must be feeling right now.

408
00:24:32.554 --> 00:24:33.847
If he's even alive.

409
00:24:35.349 --> 00:24:40.521
- I know how important he is to you.
- It's not just that he's family. Amanda.

410
00:24:42.648 --> 00:24:43.899
He's a bright light.

411
00:24:44.525 --> 00:24:49.488
Will. you'll find him. You just
have to hold on to that light.

412
00:24:51.782 --> 00:24:54.827
You're the most stubborn
person I know. After me.

413
00:24:57.204 --> 00:25:01.333
Never let anyone make you forget it.

414
00:25:04.545 --> 00:25:06.005
But first…

415
00:25:07.047 --> 00:25:09.008
Get healthy.

416
00:25:09.967 --> 00:25:11.760
Call me if you need anything.

417
00:25:15.556 --> 00:25:19.226
And if the phone rings. be careful. will.

418
00:25:22.187 --> 00:25:23.439
I will.

419
00:25:24.898 --> 00:25:26.150
Okay.

420
00:25:30.779 --> 00:25:33.407
What?

421
00:25:34.575 --> 00:25:38.829
Yes. I know. Don't bite me. okay?

422
00:25:44.626 --> 00:25:46.670
You're here to see that psycho alien girl?

423
00:25:47.171 --> 00:25:49.631
That girl can hear you. asshole.

424
00:25:50.382 --> 00:25:54.470
Never denigrate a victim
again. You're relieved.

425
00:26:04.938 --> 00:26:08.734
I am sorry about that officer. I'm
gonna have them send someone else.

426
00:26:10.235 --> 00:26:12.654
- It's okay.
- No. No. it's not. grace.

427
00:26:14.615 --> 00:26:19.661
That's your name. isn't it? Grace
elverton from minot. north Dakota?

428
00:26:21.413 --> 00:26:26.102
I spoke with your parents. and
they are so relieved that you're alive.

429
00:26:30.214 --> 00:26:32.317
I don't want to see them.

430
00:26:32.341 --> 00:26:35.528
Grace. if there is any reason why
they are not safe for you to go back to.

431
00:26:35.552 --> 00:26:36.553
- then you need...
- no.

432
00:26:37.137 --> 00:26:39.264
That's not it.

433
00:26:41.850 --> 00:26:43.811
I don't want them to see me…

434
00:26:45.187 --> 00:26:46.313
like this.

435
00:26:48.524 --> 00:26:50.859
Listen. all they care
about is that you're okay.

436
00:26:53.028 --> 00:26:55.322
They're buying their
plane tickets right now.

437
00:26:57.491 --> 00:26:58.575
Do they know…

438
00:26:59.993 --> 00:27:00.994
What happened?

439
00:27:05.040 --> 00:27:06.917
But your story is yours to tell.

440
00:27:08.710 --> 00:27:11.421
It might take a while until
you're ready. and that's okay.

441
00:27:15.592 --> 00:27:16.593
They weren't…

442
00:27:18.053 --> 00:27:19.054
Aliens.

443
00:27:23.100 --> 00:27:25.018
But how could people have done that?

444
00:27:27.354 --> 00:27:28.689
I don't know. grace.

445
00:27:30.774 --> 00:27:32.526
But it was not your fault.

446
00:27:36.446 --> 00:27:38.156
May I. please?

447
00:27:41.785 --> 00:27:45.330
The other girls. I'm
trying to help them too.

448
00:27:46.206 --> 00:27:49.686
So can you tell me
more? Who was doing this?

449
00:27:49.710 --> 00:27:51.670
There were four of them.

450
00:27:53.338 --> 00:27:55.465
Bad. bad men.

451
00:27:56.633 --> 00:27:59.469
They gave me this.

452
00:28:04.182 --> 00:28:06.560
- What did they look like?
- Three of them were short.

453
00:28:07.936 --> 00:28:09.980
But one was tall.

454
00:28:12.065 --> 00:28:13.150
Really tall.

455
00:28:15.527 --> 00:28:17.154
He was the worst one.

456
00:28:18.322 --> 00:28:19.573
Do you know his name?

457
00:28:20.866 --> 00:28:23.386
- No.
- How did they move you? How often?

458
00:28:23.410 --> 00:28:25.370
Every couple of weeks.

459
00:28:26.246 --> 00:28:29.166
All together in a truck.

460
00:28:29.791 --> 00:28:32.210
Like. a moving truck.

461
00:28:33.170 --> 00:28:34.504
It was awful.

462
00:28:36.465 --> 00:28:39.092
- I was so scared.
- And you were brave.

463
00:28:40.177 --> 00:28:43.639
You escaped. And now you're safe.

464
00:28:46.642 --> 00:28:47.643
Okay?

465
00:28:50.520 --> 00:28:51.521
You're safe.

466
00:28:52.940 --> 00:28:54.417
Okay. rocky. What do you got?

467
00:28:54.441 --> 00:28:58.713
Well. there's no camera on the
hotel itself. Just the street nearby.

468
00:28:58.737 --> 00:29:00.256
Can we make a list of all the box trucks

469
00:29:00.280 --> 00:29:01.925
that passed by the
night of Denise's death?

470
00:29:01.949 --> 00:29:03.635
It's a busy street. That's
gonna be something

471
00:29:03.659 --> 00:29:05.553
like a thousand vehicles.

472
00:29:05.577 --> 00:29:09.140
We need a better idea of when
they moved the girls. narrow it down.

473
00:29:09.164 --> 00:29:11.267
I could take another
run at the hotel clerk.

474
00:29:11.291 --> 00:29:13.519
Maybe his little taste of
lockup jogged his memory.

475
00:29:13.543 --> 00:29:16.230
Shelly talked about
transmitting signals into space.

476
00:29:16.254 --> 00:29:18.232
but how would she
know if aliens responded?

477
00:29:18.256 --> 00:29:19.734
She said she didn't
have any video cameras.

478
00:29:19.758 --> 00:29:22.820
Yeah. I'm not talking about
video. I'm talking about audio.

479
00:29:22.844 --> 00:29:24.721
Does this look like a microphone to you?

480
00:29:26.390 --> 00:29:28.892
Shelly. you paranoid genius.

481
00:29:29.518 --> 00:29:32.997
Wait. wait. wait. Okay. Listen to this.

482
00:29:35.148 --> 00:29:37.067
That's the box truck.

483
00:29:39.361 --> 00:29:40.421
That's the aliens.

484
00:29:40.445 --> 00:29:41.881
I'm cold.

485
00:29:41.905 --> 00:29:43.591
That's it. What time was that?

486
00:29:43.615 --> 00:29:45.075
Check it against the cameras.

487
00:29:46.451 --> 00:29:48.680
Get me a truck company
name and a license plate.

488
00:29:48.704 --> 00:29:50.956
We're gonna track these bastards down.

489
00:30:03.760 --> 00:30:07.389
So. that's the commander? A child?

490
00:30:09.099 --> 00:30:13.437
"Beware of false prophets who
come to you in sheep's clothing.

491
00:30:14.312 --> 00:30:18.025
but inwardly are ravenous wolves."

492
00:30:59.107 --> 00:31:02.277
Ormewood. That man is very tall.

493
00:31:03.779 --> 00:31:06.823
